      <h3>Circulation Policy</h3>
      <p>
	<ol>
	  <li>Libraries may request a maximum of 2 blocks at a time.</li>
	  <li>Blocks are circulated for a 6-month loan period.</li>
	  <li>If a particular language is not available at the time of the request, a hold will be placed on the next available block and the material will be sent accordingly.</li>
	  <li>Each block contains 30 books of the same language with a mix of fiction and non-fiction.</li>
	  <li>Each block will be sent with an instruction sheet indicating the proper procedures for handling the enclosed material.  Please follow these instructions.</li>
	  <li>A customer comment form may be included with the block; if so, please fill it out and return it with the block.</li>
	  <li>Returning supplemental blocks: Borrowing libraries must make every effort to return the complete contents of the supplemental block. If you are unable to retrieve outstanding block items from your patrons after several attempts to do so, please return the remainder of the block contents to Winnipeg Public Library with a note indicating any missing items.  The borrowing library will need to return all outstanding items to WPL individually as able, at the borrowing library's own cost.</li>
	</ol>
